SECTION-BY-SECTION CONSTRUCTION SPEC:

1) NAME BLOCK

```text
FULL NAME
Professional Title / Positioning Line
City, Country · Phone · Email · LinkedIn · Website
````

Rules:

* Name is the largest element on page.
* Name must align to main content left edge.
* Title line sits directly below name.
* Contact line sits below title with restrained spacing.
* Contact line should read as a compact metadata strip, not body text.
* All items must be vertically aligned to same left edge.
* No extra decorative treatments beyond optional thin divider below header.

2. PHOTO BLOCK

```text
┌──────────────────┐
│                  │
│   HEADSHOT       │
│   RECTANGLE      │
│                  │
└──────────────────┘
```

Rules:

* Photo aligned inside header region.
* Top of photo should roughly align with top third of name block area.
* Bottom of photo should not drop so low that it collides with summary start.
* Keep clear space between photo and contact line.
* Do not place text underneath photo within header if it creates awkward white holes.

3. DIVIDER RULE

```text
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
```

Rules:

* Use a single thin line only.
* Full usable width or optically aligned width.
* Must sit below header, not above it.
* Space above and below rule must be consistent.

4. PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY BLOCK

```text
PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY
Short paragraph of 3–5 lines with concise executive positioning.
```

Rules:

* Heading above paragraph.
* Heading aligned left.
* Paragraph width uses normal single-column measure.
* Do not narrow the paragraph unnecessarily to avoid imbalance with full-page grid.
* Summary should visually read as one compact text block.

5. CORE COMPETENCIES BLOCK

Preferred visual option:

```text
CORE COMPETENCIES
Business Development · Commercial Strategy · Stakeholder Management · Negotiation
Client Relationship Management · Process Improvement · Forecasting · CRM Management
Cross-functional Leadership · Market Analysis
```

Alternate option:

```text
CORE COMPETENCIES
Business Development                  Stakeholder Management
Commercial Strategy                  Contract Negotiation
Pipeline Management                  Market Analysis
Process Improvement                  Client Relationship Management
```

Rules:

* Keep it airy and compact.
* No bullets unless necessary.
* No progress indicators.
* No icons.
* Keep all items role-relevant.

6. PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE BLOCK

Each role should follow this exact wire structure:

```text
ROLE TITLE                                                            MMM YYYY – MMM YYYY
Company Name, Location
Optional company descriptor if context is needed
• Action + scope/context + measurable result
• Action + scope/context + measurable result
• Action + scope/context + measurable result
• Action + scope/context + measurable result
```

Expanded spacing model:

```text
PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE

ROLE TITLE                                                            MMM YYYY – Present
Company Name, Location
Optional one-line descriptor
• Bullet 1
• Bullet 2
• Bullet 3
• Bullet 4

ROLE TITLE                                                            MMM YYYY – MMM YYYY
Company Name, Location
• Bullet 1
• Bullet 2
• Bullet 3
• Bullet 4
```

Rules:

* Role title and date share same line.
* Date sits flush right.
* Company line below role title.
* Location follows company name on same line unless too long.
* Optional descriptor must be visually secondary.
* Bullets align to body text edge, not too deeply indented.
* Bullets should have consistent hanging indent.
* Space between roles must be larger than space between bullets.

7. EDUCATION BLOCK

```text
EDUCATION
Degree / Qualification                                                 YYYY – YYYY
Institution, Location
Optional honors / GPA / notable module if relevant
```

Rules:

* Keep concise.
* Same date alignment logic as experience.
* If multiple qualifications, newest first.

8. CERTIFICATIONS BLOCK

```text
CERTIFICATIONS
Certification Name — Issuer — Year
Certification Name — Issuer — Year
```

Rules:

* Use plain text lines.
* Do not over-design this section.

9. LANGUAGES BLOCK

```text
LANGUAGES
English — Native | German — Professional Working Proficiency | Swedish — Conversational
```

Rules:

* Single line or wrapped cleanly to second line.
* No bars, dots, flags, or stars.

10. TECHNICAL SKILLS BLOCK

```text
TECHNICAL SKILLS
Salesforce · HubSpot · Excel · Power BI · Microsoft 365 · Google Workspace
```

Rules:

* Prefer grouped keywords.
* Avoid dense comma-only lists if readability suffers.

11. ADDITIONAL INFORMATION BLOCK

```text
ADDITIONAL INFORMATION
Award Name — Year
Professional Membership — Status
Volunteer Position — Organization
```

Rules:

* Include only if genuinely value-adding.
* This section should never visually dominate.

VERTICAL SPACING BLUEPRINT:

Use this order and rhythm:

```text
[Top margin]
Header content
small gap
Header divider rule
medium gap
Section heading
small gap
Section content
medium gap
Section heading
small gap
Section content
medium gap
...
[Bottom margin]
```

Suggested spacing values translated into design logic:

* gap between section heading and section content: 4–8 pt
* gap between summary and competencies: 12–16 pt
* gap between competencies and experience heading: 12–16 pt
* gap between experience entries: 10–14 pt
* gap between bullets inside role: 2–4 pt
* gap between final section and bottom margin: visually balanced, never cramped

HORIZONTAL ALIGNMENT RULES:

Everything aligns to a disciplined system:

```text
LEFT EDGE OF NAME
LEFT EDGE OF TITLE
LEFT EDGE OF CONTACT LINE
LEFT EDGE OF SUMMARY HEADING
LEFT EDGE OF SUMMARY PARAGRAPH
LEFT EDGE OF ALL SECTION HEADINGS
LEFT EDGE OF ROLE TITLES
LEFT EDGE OF COMPANY LINES
LEFT EDGE OF BULLET TEXT
LEFT EDGE OF EDUCATION/CERTIFICATION/LANGUAGE CONTENT
```

Right-edge rhythm:

```text
RIGHT EDGE OF PHOTO
RIGHT EDGE OF DATE COLUMN
RIGHT EDGE OF PAGE CONTENT FIELD
```

Rules:

* Date alignment must be consistent across all entries.
* Do not let dates float inconsistently by role.
* Do not center anything except only if an explicit market convention demands it, which is not the default here.

READABILITY / SCAN PATTERN GOAL:

The eye should scan in this order:

```text
1. Full Name
2. Professional Title
3. Contact details
4. Photo confirmation
5. Summary
6. Competencies
7. Current role
8. Prior roles
9. Education
10. Supporting sections
```

The first 6–8 seconds should reveal:

* who the candidate is
* what level they are
* what role family they fit
* where to contact them
* current/recent experience
* general degree of polish and seriousness

